5. Fix `TestRegisterFileViewRoutes`: use non-previewable extension or expect 200
6. Read `scripts/test-repo-api-tokens.sh` â€” find the 3 failing assertions
7. Fix token test assertions: accept 404 in dev mode (add comment explaining why)
8. Read `scripts/test-file-history.sh` â€” find the revert test
9. Fix revert test: add `conflict_policy=replace` to the revert request
10. Run Go unit tests: `go test ./internal/api/v2/... -run 'TestViewFile|TestRegisterFileView' -v`
11. Run full Go test suite: `go test ./internal/api/v2/... -v` â€” verify zero regressions
12. Run integration tests: `bash scripts/test-repo-api-tokens.sh` and `bash scripts/test-file-history.sh`
13. Run full integration suite: `bash scripts/test.sh api` â€” verify zero regressions

**IMPORTANT:** This is a containerized project. Go tests must run inside Docker:
- Use: `docker run --rm -v ... golang:1.25-trixie go test ...`
- OR build with: `docker build -t sesamefs-gotest ... && docker run --rm sesamefs-gotest`
- Integration tests run on the host with `bash scripts/test-*.sh` (backend must be running via docker compose)

Expected result:
- All 7 previously failing assertions now pass
- All existing tests continue to pass (zero regressions)
- Test expectations match actual correct handler behavior

